caption: I don’t know why it takes more than 13 minutes to pour an ice coffee and put it ion the pickup shelf. I left it since I was in a hurry and couldn’t wait anymore.
Good coffee and sandwiches
Great pastries!

Collective Coffee on Damen street is one of my favorite coffee shops in the area. The staff is super friendly and kind. The coffee and beverages are always hot and tasty. The bakery items are super delicious. I recommend the Blueberry Lemon Scone and The Morning Glory Muffin. I enjoy the open space and plants in the shop.
Good coffee and a dog friendly pick up window!
Amazing space, great people, love the drinks!!
Awesome coffee spot with a great patio and pick up area (so I can walk my pup there)

Colectivo Coffee - Wicker Park is a great small coffee shop to get some work done or catch up with a friend.  The ambiance is very cozy thanks to the natural light filtering in during the day (or semi-bright lighting at night time), quaint wooden furniture, and knick knacks decorating the area.
The pie spice latte is so good!
Great app and pickup system. Delicious cappuccinos, breakfast burritos, coffee beans and muffins. If you haven't tried this coffee, do yourself a favor and stop by.

Such a great atmosphere, great seating options for COVID. The staff is great, food selection is awesome, I always get the potato bacon burrito, it comes with a light red salsa and it's delicious! Bakery items are 🤌🤌🤌 but that Mexicana mocha latte is spicy AF jsyk

Such a cute coffeehouse! The bacon egg cheese English muffin sandwich is delish!! Also, the salted chocolate chip walnut cookie is one of the best chocolate chip cookies I’ve ever had! Oh, and their coffee is really good. Very strong but good.

Not the best first experience.  Came over here to get breakfast and study on a Saturday morning. Come to find out they turn off their WiFi on Saturday so I wasn’t able to get any work done. Also, after I ordered a breakfast sandwich and sat down, someone came over and told me they were out of eggs. They serve breakfast all day... 🤦🏼‍♀️  Update: Recently moved and now live very close to this place. They’re pickup services have been amazing during the pandemic and such a time saver. I just use the app to order, get an email when it’s ready, walk over and grab it. Cappuccinos are good and the peppermint fluff latte is amazing. Once the pandemic is over though, it would be great if WiFi is on all the time 😬

My wife and I were so excited to visit this place. I rarely, if ever, write poor reviews but we had such a rough experience back in March. We came just before the lockdown and they forgot my order. The staff acted annoyed to make it for me then placed it without putting in a straw, like they did with every other customer. I didn't want to reach over as I understood new measures were taking place to be sanitary and avoid customers grabbing a straw container. They walked away as I asked for one, so after waiting another minute being stared at by everyone, I reached for one and got called out by the employee. I trust that it was just a bad day and people were scared looking for a scapegoat. The drinks itself were delicious and my wife and I loved the setting, but in the start of the pandemic, as an Asian-American, I felt terrible and my wife stepped out saying, "wow." My wife says Collectivo was her first experience seeing the discomfort of being married to an Asian directly. Would definitely go back for the amazing drinks with someone else grabbing take out for me or just visiting after the pandemic

The lady that was serving me gave me a chocolate croissant when I asked for the chocolate chip cookie clearly twice, and she ignored me the first time, and it took them almost 20 min to get a cup of coffee ready.

Boutique Coffee shop based out of Milwaukee, Wisconsin.  So glad they are in Chicago, move over Starbucks this is my new go to coffeehouse.  Their secret is the freshness of the roast. I've been drinking their Blue Heeler Coffee blend for a few years. Menu adds pastry and sandwiches that include a Impossible Breakfast Muffin. Various locations
I love their coffee and food, but the wait here on a Saturday morning is unacceptably long. They are overwhelmed by in-person and app orders. I won't be coming back here on the weekend for a while.

the staff here are very friendly and knowledgeable. when I have asked whether they have unwashed / natural process beans they are not confused what I'm asking about, and can speak to the characteristics of each. the outdoor area has a good amount of distanced seating. their coffee is very good, both what they serve and when you get a bag of takeaway. they also offer curbside pickup
Buzzin’
Cool people drinking hot coffee and distancing. Needs a bike rack.

Let me preface this by saying all the staff I interacted with were lovely.  I ordered coffee and a burrito. The coffee was hot. Too hot to hold. No worries right? I'll just get a sleeve. Wrong, still too hot to handle. No worries right? I'll just put it in the bag I'm carrying. Wrong. On my walk home the bag broke. The coffee inside was still so hot that it burnt my foot through my shoe and sock. This was 10 minutes later. Coffee is supposed to be hot, I obviously get that. Not that hot though.
Great coffee and nice people, nice place to chill 🙃

Collectivo in Wicker Park is a great spot to grab a coffee and meet with a friend or get some work done for an hour or two. I can't wait until the patio opens again so there is even more space available!
it had a good atmosphere and good service, very cool architecture. but it was very crowded and very democrat/liberal focused, which is a downside.
Always super polite, great coffee, great tea, great atmosphere. You can be anyone here and they are super kind (they are super respectful towards like LGBTQ+)

Awesome coffee shop and spot to work in Wicker Park. Their coffee is great and they have a really nice selection of pastries. The prepared food can be hit or miss but I've found my favorites like the curry wrap. We come here early with my young son and hang by the fireplace (in winter) or the patio (in summer). I love that the entire front of the place opens up, especially on nice days. Be careful coming after 10am on a weekday because this place gets super busy with people working.
I love their teas.

The coffee, food, staff and atmosphere are great... The WiFi sucks. Drops after about 45 mins of use and won't reconnect except in short durations. Really blows if you're on a Skype call or streaming something.
Love the atmosphere and staff. It's a bit over priced though.
Great coffee. Great avocado toast. Friendly staff. Good place to work too
Yummy coffee + a great place to hang out whether you want a comfy couch to relax or a table and wifi to get work done
Easy spot to grab coffee, snack & pastries, 2 levels & a fireplace hideaway. Lots of people working on laptops, getting stuff done.
Nice

The staff made rude and sarcastic comments about my coffee order . All I asked for was steamed milk with my drip coffee. I’ve been ordering this in shops around Chicago for years and no one bats an eye. The barista with bleached short blonde hair seemed so be particularly inconvenienced by this. I felt like I was in an episode of Curb your Enthusiasm. One star because the at least the scone was tasty.
Great atmosphere. Nice looking people. Friendly staff. Free wifi. Plenty of room to work.

Excited to try this place out since we were in the neighborhood and it was a cold evening. We get to the register and the woman taking the order (short bleach blond hair) was extremely cold and rude. Didn’t even look at us while she took our order. Gave our order in to go go cups while the group of individuals in front us got glass wear. Didn’t ask if it was “for here” or “to go”. Coffee is great but the staff not so much.
It’s my first time in this brunch. Colective is so good but this brunch is superior the design is great. Also, the staff are friendly

Delicious coffee, great vibe and setting for work. But they have the dumbest, most frustrating wifi policy ever. From 12 until 2p on Saturdays, they just turn it off... they claim that they do this out of convenience for their customers. So they simply don't have customers during those hours.

Can improve on their internet connectivity. I know it disconnects after each hour but it is slow and unstable. I am just not able to do office work- a light internet browsing might work. Apart from that I like the space and their coffee.
Great place, service and seating area are amazing.
Nice coffee shop

This place is great. I love their coffee but their customer service is out of this world. I had a latte last week that didn’t taste like it usually does so I called to let them know. Not only were they super nice about the call they also asked me to come back and get it again. Then when I came they went above and beyond to make sure I was satisfied. And this latte was so good! I’m very pleased and will be a loyal customer.
I like this place, especially the sofas near the fireplace, where is so cozy and hygge. Also, they have many veggie options.
Great coffee and funky atmosphere

Great coffee/cafe spot. They have Vegetarian and Vegan options for food/pastries-- also the Oat Milk Lattes are delicious!  Only issue here is they charge extra for oat milk (WHY?) and are pricey for the food (although delicious) they dont give you a whole lot for what you pay. [Sesame sweet potatoe bowl is over $9.00 and tiny portions]. Also, if you plan on doing work here, the outlet game is scarce and music can be pretty loud. The WiFi kicks you off after an hour it's really annoying.
I like this place... Very chilled atmosphere with good, chilled music. The shop creates a productive environment.
Great place for coffee and work on relax days.
(Translated by Google) Excellent place the coffee is good and there is free wifi 😁  (Original) Excelente lugar el café es bueno y hay wifi gratis 😁

No WiFi between 10-2pm on weekends?! Poor business model, and this Wicker Park location was half empty this morning, so you can’t even justify keeping customer flow by limiting WiFi for paying costumers. Totally contradicts your space. It’s almost 2020 and you play childish WiFi games with customers who pay $$ for coffee?  I’d fire those who decided this policy. Business success is based in good costumer Service.
Great coffee with surprisingly good food options, also comes with alot of work room. Only thing I would say is the music is not great for a typical coffee shop. So bring your headphones!
They are the most enjoyable spaces in the city. Plus the have a good food selection and many choices of coffee types. This is one of a handful of great places
I had a great meal the food was excellent. I will go back again.
My favorite place to go and study!! Great coffee - try the horchata cold brew. Nice staff too

This review is mostly for the ambiance and not so much for their drinks/food. I was looking for a coffee shop with an outdoor patio and stumbled across this place on yelp. So glad my friend and I decided to come here because they have an amazing outdoor patio! Perfect for the summer! I got their summer gala drink which was perfectly refreshing to sip on while catching up with my friend and enjoying the beautiful weather. Not only is their outdoor space wonderful but the interior is gorgeous! It's quite spacious with 2 levels and looks very modern yet cozy. Probably a great place to work/study. Will definitely come back!
Love the coffee and food. Very popular but the staff is friendly and helpful so it never takes too long to get your drinks. Great place to hang out but a little loud if you're looking to study
Such great musiiiiiiic!!! A good vibe for meetings, creative work. Seating is NOT comfortable, but the overall atmosphere and look is great.

A nice place to work, with reliable internet, good tunes (though maybe a bit loud for me sometimes),  and so many different sections and types of seating (patio, upper deck with roll up doors, work bench with stools, main floor with high tops, cozy chairs, or communal tables) that you can always find something that suits your mood. Big affordable mugs of coffee and speciality drinks, plus lots of actual food options.

Stopped in on the second day of their grand opening. We arrived pretty early and it was already super packed. I got the egg bites and a lemonade and the bf got an americano. All the food and drinks were quite good, we really liked this location. The only reason I took off 1 star is bc of how annoyingly packed it got in there, but that's not necessarily a bad thing, in fact, it's great for the coffee shop! I just tend to dislike spots that get insanely and annoyingly packed w people. Also, it was more expensive than most coffee shops. That being said, we will be back!
Good cappuccino, and delicious food. The patio is amazing.
Love the decor and so much open space !

A really fitting sister location to the Logan Square's Colectivo- an equally well run, delightful spot for tasty eats, coffee, a brew both cold and on tap or a delicious serving of bottled kombucha, if that's what you're into. The Troubadour baked goods never disappoint and food-wise there are a few really great vegetarian choices, if you're meat free. The Wicker Park location also has an indoor/outdoor porch that you'll enjoy if you like to be slightly elevated for your fresh air moment. Also, the staff always come off real, friendly but also professional; an all around welcome vibe. You should definitely stop in for a nibble and a mini hang by yourself or with a friend
This is my favorite coffee spot in the city.
I’m profoundly frustrated by the lack of WiFi 10 - 2 on Saturdays.
Apparently they were tired so the coffee must not be very good. Wouldn't know though since they closed early.
The best Colectivo location I've ever been to! Staff was friendly and the atmosphere was incredible. It's catered toward people working on their laptops and that is perfect for me!
Wicked spot
Nice place to chill and do some work. Although the wifi is spotty at best :/ Good 'sports tea'.
Had the mango peach ginger smoothie. A bit spicy and refreshing.
Try the horchata cold brew!
Friendliest staff. Amazing coffee. Wonderful environment. Great sweets. Salmon sandwich is delicious.
Love the coffee! Not a lot of outlets for those looking to spend a few hours on the computer.  Seating is very close too, so not a lot of privacy.

Stopped here for breakfast. I asked for a recommendation for something vegetarian and dairy free. They recommended the Veggie Pesto Burrito. I double checked with them that the pesto didn't have any dairy and there was no other dairy in the burrito. I got my food, and it looked like there was cheese in it. I took it back to ask them, and they said that that was just the egg. I took a bite of the food, and knew it was cheese, and took it back once again.  They said it was cheese and they had been wondering if it had cheese but weren't sure so they didn't say anything.  Definitely do not come here if you have any allergies unless you want overpriced coffee and food (for small quantities) and staff who don't know the ingredients in the food they serve.
Great coffee, good beer and awesome service.
Super tasty ice tea with some bite to it. Good looking space with an airy ascending stair case.
Really nice coffee place! Delicious coffee, nice big space inside and outside and also outside. Will definitely come back to try other drinks!
Something different then Starbucks. in hot day try espresso frap.
Super cute and nice outdoor seating. Tasty coffee.
Awesome spot. Killer coffee & food. I get their cappuccino.
I love this place
Great coffee, location, ambiance and the best dream bar I ever had!

Sparkling Cherry Cold Brew is a new summer addiction! This location has a great patio with tons of indoor and outdoor seating. Large selection of baked goods and a nice menu with decent amount of variety. Only issue can be slow service at times. Lately I have gone in and waited quite a bit to order, as only one person was working counter. I wouldn’t mind if they were short staffed but there have been at least 3-4 other staff members hanging behind counter. Don’t see why one can’t jump in if they see there is a struggling customer at the counter. Other than that, consistent coffee and nice atmosphere!
Cozy neighborhood cafe with very pleasant and friendly staff.

Great atmosphere! Friendly staff with vibrant attitudes. Coffee is just right, down to a science. Some vegan options and an ideal space to do work. Easy to get to via the Damen 50, Division 70 buses, or by bike. Close to an ATM and just South of six corners in Wicker Park. See you there!
Amazing place
Cozy and peaceful space with good coffee. Nice break from the chaos outside of the doors. Outdoor seating.
Excellent spacious hip coffee shop
Love the location.
Great spot to stop in to do work, but the wifi really needs some improvement.  It is spotty and cuts out constantly in the middle of working on things.

It's a great space and I'm so happy to have it in the neighborhood; however, the service can be kind of rude, stand-offish.  This is a friendly place, and some of the staff have a snobby coffee shop vibe.  It's really off-putting when I come in the staff doesn't smile or say thank you.
Open, airy and very pleasant.
Great coffee mysogynistic manager.
Great environment. Nice upstairs seating. Had the nitro which was solid.
It's the best enviromment great food and coffee is better than Intelligentsia

Sorely needed coffee shop with great seating capacity. Easily the best coffee shop in the neighborhood!
Just a quiet and comfortable place where you  can enjoy  wakening  up with  a good breakfast
Sorry but no wifi allowed on Saturday?
Good atmosphere and lots of seating- berry lemonade iced tea tasted like cough medicine tho
(Translated by Google) A cozy place, good and fast attention. Excellent sweets  (Original) Un lugar acogedor, buena y rápida atención. Dulces excelentes.

Cool, airy layout with 2 floors of seating.  The tea was great, the food also (try the frittatas!) and service was good.  However, I have 2 suggestions to improve the experience.  1. Please turn the base down ... I was vibrating in my seat the whole time ... music volume also a bit much considering many people go to cafes to study or do work; when I asked if this could be adjusted, I was told that the music is "controlled from Milwaukee headquarters" - seems odd.  2. WIFI was spotty and consistently slow during my visit (1-5pm on a weekday).  Overall, I'm excited to have this new edition to my neighborhood but hoping suggestions will be considered.
I am from Miami, FL and starting to love this place. Everyday it’s a new vibe ✅💙

Brand new location of one of my favorite coffee shops. This is by far the largest I’ve web and beautifully designed + reliably delicious coffee and treats. Two floors, tons of seating indoor and out and all size tables, two rooms that can be made private, outdoor patio and lounge area near the fireplace. Already packed on its opening weekend, destine to be a neighborhood favorite.
There could be more charging but plenty of seating. Beautiful new place in a perfect location

So excited Colectivo opened in Wicker Park. Been waiting for this for a couple of months. I was not disappointed when I tried it, the coffee is great, baked goods are amazing and the ambiance is so cozy. New favorite coffee shop.
